<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Urges Israel to Comply With New Wye Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
Chairman Yasser Arafat called on Israel Sunday to sincerly
implement the revised version of the Wye agreement signed on
Sunday in Sharm El-Sheikh, Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Upon his return from Rome where he briefed Pope John Paul II on
the document, Arafat told reporters at his office here Sunday
evening that the new accord "entrusts us with a new responsibility
to go on the way."
</P>
<P>
Arafat recalled the Berlin Declaration, the address of United
States President Bill Clinton last April and the message he
received from U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In the Berlin Declaration issued last March, the European Union
asserted support for the Palestinian people's right to
statehood.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said last April the Palestinian people had the right to
enjoy freedom on their free land.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Albright handed message to Arafat guaranteeing
Israel's withdrawal from the West Bank according to the newly-set
timetable.
</P>
<P>
However, Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said in Sunday's
meeting of his cabinet which ratified the new agreement that the
agreement allows Israel to postpone the redeployment to hold more
intensive negotiations in the final status stage with the
Palestinians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
