<DOCNO> XIE19990906.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Welcomes Other Europeans to Join French Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The French Minister of Economy
and Finance Dominique Strauss-Kahn said on Sunday that France
welcomes other Europeans to ally with the banks of Banque
Nationale de Paris (BNP) and the Societe Generale (SG), now that
they have finished their merge battle.
</P>
<P>
The BNP will take over a majority of shares of another bank,
Paribas, and will have about 38 percent of the shares of SG, after
half a year of merge battle among them.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the French television channel TF1,
Strauss-Kahn said that the French government had prevented any
foreign bank or speculator from intervening during the merge
operation, in fear of destabilizing the country's financial
situation.
</P>
<P>
``I don't want that at a moment when the French enterprises are
solving their own problems, they are attacked from outside,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that from now on, France welcomes its ``European
allies'' to join the BNP or SG on an equal footing.
</P>
<P>
The minister added that the role of government in the merge
operations of enterprises was to arbitrate or mediate instead of
becoming a direct actor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
