<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti-Sino Relations Excellent: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Deputy Prime
Minister and Defense Minister Salem Al-Sabah said here Sunday
that the relations between Kuwait and China are excellent.
</P>
<P>
Salem made the comments to Xinhua at the airport before
leaving for China and South Korea for an official visit.
</P>
<P>
He said he was very pleased to visit China again and
would like to thank the Chinese government and the people of
China, including the parliament members, for the attitude they
took towards the issue of Kuwaiti prisoners of war (POWs).
</P>
<P>
Salem said he would raise the humanitarian issue again
during his talks with senior Chinese officials, expressing
belief that Beijing would "look into it in the United
Nations Security Council."
</P>
<P>
Kuwait insists that Iraq is still detaining over 600
Kuwaiti and third country nationals snatched on the streets by
Iraqi troops during Iraq's occupation of Kuwait in 1990-1991.
</P>
<P>
In response to the question about his specific agenda in
China, Salem said there are "a lot of things in the plates
of both sides." But he did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
However, in his statement to Kuwait News Agency Saturday,
the Kuwaiti defense chief said he would hold talks with
Chinese leaders on ways of cementing bilateral relations in
various fields, especially the military and defense ties.
</P>
<P>
He will also visit Chinese military facilities, military
units as well as military hospitals and clinics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
