<HEADLINE> Britain Condemns Car Bombings in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 5 (Xinhua) - Britain on Sunday condemned the
suspected car bombings in two northern Israeli towns which killed
at least three people inside the vehicles.
</P>
<P>
"I was horrified by the news of today's car bomb attacks in
Israel," Foreign Office Minister Peter Hain said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The British government condemned "all acts of terrorism", the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
"The fact that these attacks may have been aimed at unsettling
the Middle East peace process is deplorable," Hain said.
</P>
<P>
He said the Middle East peace process made significant progress
on Saturday with the signing by Israel and the Palestine Authority
of the agreement to implement the Wye Memorandum.
</P>
<P>
"Such acts(the bombings) will only serve to harden the resolve
of those in the region and elsewhere in their search for a
comprehensive, just and lasting peaceful settlement," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
