<HEADLINE> French Socialist Party Urges U.N. Intervention in East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- France's ruling Socialist Party
First Secretary Francois Hollande Sunday urged the United Nations
to intervene in East Timor immediately to stop the violence there.
</P>
<P>
Some 120 people have been killed by anti-independence
militiamen in East Timor after a majority of the population there
voted for independence of the province from Indonesia this week.
</P>
<P>
``In the name of the Socialist Party, I wish that the U.N.
intervene before it is too late. There should be absolutely an
intervention force,'' Hollande told Europe 1 radio.
</P>
<P>
He also condemned the 25 years of Indonesian rule in East Timor
as ``one of the biggest scandals of international life.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
