Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy expressed "serious concern"
over the two incidents, urged the Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) to take tough measures to curb terrorism.
(BC-Israel-Bombings)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak ordered a swift
investigation into two ill-fated car bombings in northern Israel
Sunday afternoon, saying that Israel would not tolerate any
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
"A major incident has been averted with the perpetrators
possibly killed...The Israeli government will not tolerate any
terror act against its citizens," Barak's office said in a
statement in response to the two car bombings.
(BC-Israel-Bombings)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Palestinian National Authority Chairman Yasser Arafat
called on Israel Sunday to sincerly implement the revised version
of the Wye agreement signed on Sunday in Sharm El-Sheikh, Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Upon his return from Rome where he briefed Pope John Paul II on
the document, Arafat told reporters at his office here Sunday
evening that the new accord "entrusts us with a new responsibility
