<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 25,000 People Affected with HIV/AIDS in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 5 (Xinhua) -- A recent study carried out
in Nepal showed that about 25,000 Nepalese have been affected with
HIV/AIDS (Human Immunodeficiency Virus and Human Immunodeficiency
Syndrome), the official RSS news agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to National AIDS and Study Control Center, Nepal,
1,312 people have so far been officially recorded as HIV positive,
of which 137 have already died.
</P>
<P>
Among those contracted with the HIV/AIDS, 312 are women
involved in prostitution, 726 men having sexual relationship with
such women, 80 housewives and 163 drug abusers.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Law and Justice Tarani Datta Chataut said at a
workshop on HIV/AIDS opened Sunday that the spread of a fatal
disease like HIV/AIDS would become a huge problem for a country
like Nepal with minimum resources and low education.
</P>
<P>
Some participants of the workshop called for the need to
generate public awareness to control the disease. Lack of the
knowledge about AIDS is one of the main reasons the disease spread
fast in Nepal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
