<HEADLINE> Shanghai Reports Industrial Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
industrial and commercial city, generated 14.68 billion yuan in
industrial added value in August, up 10.1 percent from the same
month last year.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released here today by the Shanghai
Municipal Statistics Bureau, the sales-production ratio of
Shanghai's industrial products in the month rose to a new high of
99.13 percent.
</P>
<P>
Of these products, 9.44 billion yuan worth were sold abroad, up
about 20 percent from August 1998.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also indicate that the efficiency of local
manufacturers has improved significantly, with their combined
profits rising 12.8 percent to reach 11.95 billion yuan during the
first seven months of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
