<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Governor Awarded for His Role in Hosting Horti-Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Governor Li Jiating of Yunnan
Province in southwest China was awarded a gold medal for his role
in hosting the ongoing World Horticultural Exposition in Kunming,
the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
Otto Koch, chairman of the Association Internationale des
Producteurs del'Horticulture (AIPH), presented the award at the
51st annual meeting of the AIPH, which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Koch expressed warm congratulations to the host province on its
success in sponsoring such a world-class exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Led by the central government and with the help from across the
country, Kunming spent merely three years preparing for the grand
event, while most other host countries in the past had to take
five to seven years preparing, Koch noted.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that the horticultural industry will become even
more competitive in the next century, and horticultural producers
worldwide will have to work harder to reduce costs and improve
quality.
</P>
<P>
China's horticultural industry has developed rapidly in recent
years, but Chinese horticultural workers should attach greater
importance to science and technology rather than to speed, Koch
said.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing international horticultural show began on May 1 and
will run through October 31.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
