<HEADLINE> LIFFE Lists Second Short Term Interest Rate Futures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The London International
Financial Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) Monday listed the
second of its STIR contracts, the Three Month Short Sterling
futures contract, on LIFFE ConnectTH.
</P>
<P>
It comes after the successful listing of Three Month Euroswiss
futures contract on August 23.
</P>
<P>
LIFFEE ConnectTH is an electronic trading system, designed and
developed by LIFFE in-house. It is based on an open architecture
system and uses front-end solutions developed by 15 independent
software vendors (ISVs).
</P>
<P>
LIFFE's Chief Executive, Hugh Freedberg, said "The listing of
the Three Month Euroswiss futures contract on LIFFE ConnectTH were
extremely smooth and we have been pleased with the trading volumes
since."
</P>
<P>
"The Short Sterling futures contract will be traded in parallel
with open outcry trading, which gives customers a choice of
trading platform," he added. 
</P>
