<HEADLINE> First Libyan-Made Car Goes on Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TRIPOLI, September 6 (xinhua) -- For the first time in the
automotive history, a Libyan company unveiled a prototype vehicle
Monday to mark the country's 30th anniversary of Revolution.
</P>
<P>
The car, said to be unprecedented in its high level of safety,
is produced by the Libyan Arab Domestic Investment Company
(LADICO) as the outcome of the country's Jamahiriya Rocket Vehicle
Project.
</P>
<P>
The LADICO, by far the largest stock company in Libya with a
general assembly of over 70,000 shareholders employing over 1,000
people, entered the auto industry only 4 years ago and has
established itself as the leading distributor of CBU vehicles in
the market.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the contemporary technical features such as a
four-wheel independent suspension system, four-wheel disc brakes
with anti-lock braking system, two-liter four-cylinder injection
engine, the medium-sized "libyan Rocket" incorporates leading edge
technology in safety devices both on the interior and exterior.
</P>
<P>
The project, launched two years ago, is aimed at meeting the
dire need to save the lives of thousands of Libyans from
increasing road fatalities.
</P>
<P>
And the automotive Division of the LADICO has been making
efforts to localize the country's auto industry in response to
booming demand for cars in the domestic markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
