<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Starts Australia Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MELBOURNE, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin arrived here Monday evening to begin a state visit to
Australia at the invitation of Australian Governor-General William
Patrick Deane.
</P>
<P>
This represents the first state visit to Australia by a Chinese
head of state.
</P>
<P>
Upon arrival at the airport, Jiang said in a written statement,
"My present visit to Australia is aimed at enhancing friendship,
deepening cooperation and opening up the way to the future with
the interests of the Asian-Pacific region in mind."
</P>
<P>
"I am looking forward to an extensive and in-depth exchange of
views with Australian leaders on bilateral relations and
international and regional issues of common interest in the
upcoming days, and working together to promote the all-round
development of the mutually beneficial friendly relations and
cooperation between our two countries," he added.
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced that, with the efforts of both sides, my visit
will be a complete success, and the Sino-Australian relations will
see greater development in the coming new century," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, he went on to say, with the concerted efforts
of both sides, the relations between the two nations have gained a
good momentum of all-round development.
</P>
<P>
As the two economies are highly complementary to each other, he
continued, there are broad prospects for the further expansion of
the mutually-beneficial bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"It is all the more important for China and Australia,
important countries in the Asian-Pacific region, to strengthen
contacts and develop cooperation further at the turn of the
century," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He explained this is not only in the common interests of the
two countries and two peoples, but also conducive to maintaining
and promoting peace and development in the region.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is expected to deliver a speech at a Sino-Australian
symposium on trade and investment at noon Tuesday before
proceeding to Canberra to meet Governor-General Deane and attend a
welcoming banquet in his honor.
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled to end his visit to Australia on September 11
before heading for New Zealand to start a state visit and attend
the 7th Informal Meeting of Leaders of the Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's entourage includes his wife, Wang Yeping, Vice-Premier
Qian Qichen and his wife, Zhou Hanqiong, Director of the General
Office of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee Wang Gang,
Minister in charge of the State Development Planning Commission
Zeng Peiyan, Minister in charge of the Central Foreign Affairs
Office Liu Huaqiu, Director of the Policy Research Office of the
Central Committee Teng Wensheng and Chinese Ambassador to
Australia Zhou Wenzhong.
</P>
<P>
Jiang was greeted at the Melbourne airport by Australian Deputy
Prime Minister John Anderson and Governor of Victoria State James
Bobbo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
