<HEADLINE> EU Approves Aid to World Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brussels, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
Monday that it has approved humanitarian aid worth a total of 13.
85 million euros (14.68 million U.S. dollars) for the Middle East,
Romania, the Ethiopia-Eritrea region and Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) executive branch said the aid will
support the humanitarian projects to be carried out in these areas
for up to nine months.
</P>
<P>
The aid for the Middle East region will fund projects in the
West Bank, Gaza Strip, Lebanon, Jordan and Syria ,with priorities
given to health care, assistance for the disabled, water and
sanitation, as well as rehabilitation, the commission said.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian refugees and their host countries of Lebanon,
Jordan and Syria will get a total of 11 million euros (11.66
million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Some 1.75 million euros (1.86 million dollars) in fund will
reach the disabled people in Romania, which cover food, hygiene
and other essential needs for patients in 55 institutions.
</P>
<P>
The EU assistance of 600,000 euros (636,000 U.S. dollars) will
help about a quarter of a million homeless people displaced in
border conflicts between Ethiopia and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
And a total of 500,000 euros (530,000 U.S. dollars) will be
used to evacuate residents from around Nicaragua's most active
volcano, Cerro Negro, which erupted in August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
