<HEADLINE> S. Africa Welcomes Mideast Peace Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The South African
government Monday welcomed the peace accord between Israel and the
Palestinian National Authority, saying it boded well for a just
and lasting peace.
</P>
<P>
"Both sides are to be congratulated and commended on this
significant development, and while the path toward a final status
agreement will doubtless be a difficult one, the agreement reached
at Sharm-el-Sheikh bodes well for the type of cooperation which
alone can result in the achievement of a just and lasting peace,"
the Foreign Ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
It was reacting to the accord -- signed at the Egyptian Red Sea
resort of Sharm-el-Sheikh on September 4 -- which amends the
long-delayed Wye River agreement.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls on Israel to make further troop withdrawals
from the West Bank and release hundreds of prisoners, starting
within one week.
</P>
<P>
Under the modified accord, a framework agreement on the
permanent status of the Palestinian territories should be ready in
February, with negotiations concluded within a year from now.
</P>
