<HEADLINE> Estrada Cites China as Example of Open Policy Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada has cited China, which ranks high in terms of economic
growth in Asia, as a top example of the success of market
liberalization policy while stressing the need to open up the
Philippine economy to foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
In a presidential statement released here Monday, Estrada noted
that China recorded rapid growth of gross national product after
adopting liberalization measures that brought in foreign capital,
new technologies and more jobs for its people.
</P>
<P>
"That's what China did. This move created more jobs for the
people and brought in new technologies," the president said.
</P>
<P>
He said his call for economic reforms to relax the restrictions
on foreign land ownership and equity in local businesses and
public utilities through the charter change aims to not only bring
in billions of pesos in foreign capital, and new technologies that
will modernize domestic industries but also bring down the costs
of delivering basic services to the people.
</P>
<P>
"So if we allow 100-percent foreign ownership, there will be an
influx of overseas investors along with technology transfer, which
is very important to us. This will help us a lot," the president
said in his weekly radio-TV program. 
</P>
