<HEADLINE> UK Clears Christie of Doping Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 6 (Xinhua) -- A UK Athletics disciplinary
committee cleared former Olympic champion Linford Christie of
doping charges on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 39-year-old British sprinter, the 100 meters Olympic
champion in Barcelona in 1992, attended a hearing on Friday after
he tested positive of nandrolone in February.
</P>
<P>
"The Disciplinary Committee concluded that it could not be
proven beyond reasonable doubt that the substance present in the
sample was derived from a prohibited substance. Therefore, Linford
Christie has been cleared of all charges." The British's athletics
governing body said in a statement on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Christie, now a successful coach, protested last month that he
was innocent after his urine sample showed traces of the same drug
that fellow veteran Merlene Ottey tested positive for prior to the
World Championships.
</P>
<P>
Christie failed the test at an indoor meeting in Dortmund in
February, though his positive sample was only made public on
August 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
