<HEADLINE> Eritrea Sees Ethiopia's Rejection as Declaration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Eritrea described on Monday
Ethiopia's rejection of the Technical Arrangements last Saturday
as "tantamount to a declaration of war".
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia Foreign Ministry reiterated on September 4 its
territorial demand from Eritrea while demanding interpretations
of the Technical Arrangements proposed by Organization of African
Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's rejection "indicates, without any shred of doubt,
that it is about to unleash its war of aggression", said a
statement released Monday by Eritrean Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Such a move "not only constitutes a rejection of the Technical
 Arrangements but of the entire OAU peace package", said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea accepted the Technical Arrangements on August 7, which
required two sides to respect the boundary inherited from the
colonial rule and not resort to force in resolving border
conflicts.
</P>
<P>
The border conflict broke out in early May between the two Horn
of Africa neighbors and soon escalated into a war of attrition.
</P>
