<HEADLINE> International Tourist Festival to Be Held in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September (Xinhua) -- The '99 Hangzhou Golden Autumn
International Tourist Festival is scheduled for September 17-
October 16 in the city of Hangzhou, a famous tourist destination
in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou's Vice Mayor Ye Defan said here today that the
festival will feature a series of activities such as enjoying
sweet-scented osmanthus under the full moon on West Lake,
parachute jumping, a fireworks show, and a temple fair.
</P>
<P>
An investment and trade fair will also be held during the one-
month festival, Ye said.
</P>
<P>
Some two million Chinese and overseas tourists are expected to
attend this event, according to Ye.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou initiated the festival last year.  
</P>
