<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Merchant Bank of China, one of
the country's major banking institutions, opened its full-scaled
on-line services today by signing e-business contracts with three
domestic clients.
</P>
<P>
Bank president Ma Weihua told Xinhua that in 1997 his bank
became the first in the country to open a website, and has since
been developing its on-line business step by step.
</P>
<P>
To date, the bank has on-line services including payment, stock
trading and shopping. By the end of July, 371 institutional
clients had enjoyed the bank's on-line services, with a total
trading volume of 2.7 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Customers now can even buy lottery and air ticket, make
donations, and order hotel rooms via the Internet, Ma said.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that China now has some four million
Internet users, and many local enterprises are now doing on-line
business. 
