<HEADLINE> President Jiang Sends Congratulations on OAU Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
sent a message of congratulation Monday to his Algerian
counterpart Abdelaziz Bouteflika, also Chairman of the
Organization of African Unity, on the occasion of the opening of
the OAU extraordinary summit in Sirte, Libya.
</P>
<P>
In the message, Jiang praised the OAU for its tremendous
contribution to "safeguarding the state sovereignty of African
nations, eradicating colonialism, maintaining African solidarity
and cooperation and promoting regional stability and development."
He said the summit, held at the turn of the century, would have "a
far-reaching impact on development of the African continent and
the OAU itself in the coming century."
</P>
<P>
Jiang also stressed China's independent foreign policy of
strengthening "its solidarity and cooperation with the vast number
of developing countries including those in Africa" and said China
is "ready to work together with African countries and the OAU to
bring a friendly and cooperative China-Africa relationship of long
term stability and vitality into the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
He wishes the extraordinary summit a complete success. 
</P>
