<HEADLINE> Philippine House Speaker Backs Women-Friendly Bills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Speaker Manny Villar
aired his support Monday for the passage of two "women-friendly"
bills being taken up by the House of Representatives, Philippine
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
One bill seeks to grant a one month cumulative leave with pay
to women workers who undergo major surgical operations on the
internal reproductive organs, while the other seeks to reserve
suitable parking or seating spaces for pregnant women in public
places, the report said.
</P>
<P>
"We should make a concerted effort to make things easier for
women who carry the burden of bearing children," said Villar.
</P>
<P>
Several government agencies, including the Department of the
Interior, Civil Service Commission, through their representatives
have likewise signified their support for the two bills during
committee deliberations.
</P>
<P>
Villar said the House has already passed on final reading an
Anti-discrimination bill to prevent unfair treatment of women
workers in the work-place. It was one of the more than 220 bills
and resolutions passed during the House's first regular session.
</P>
<P>
"There should be equality and justice in treating women, while
recognizing their specific and unique needs," he said, adding that
these differences "should not be used as an excuse to discriminate
against women." 
</P>
