<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin: Australia Tour to Enhance Friendship, Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MELBOURNE, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said on Monday his visit to Australia is aimed at enhancing
friendship, deepening cooperation and opening up the way to the
future with the interests of the Asian-Pacific region in mind.
</P>
<P>
He is "very pleased" to come to Melbourne to begin the state
visit at the invitation of Australian Governor-General William
Patrick Deane, Jiang said in a written statement upon arrival in
this second biggest city of Australia.
</P>
<P>
This represents the first state visit to Australia by a Chinese
head of state.
</P>
<P>
"I am looking forward to an extensive and in-depth exchange of
views with Australian leaders on bilateral relations and
international and regional issues of common interest in the
upcoming days, and working together to promote the all-round
development of the mutually beneficial friendly relations and
cooperation between our two countries," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He stated that he is also "ready to, through this opportunity,
get in touch with Australian friends from all walks of life, get a
better knowledge of and learn from the achievements and successful
experience of Australia in its nation-building effort."
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced that, with the efforts of both sides, my visit
will be a complete success, and the Sino-Australian relations will
see greater development in the coming new century," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Both China and Australia are in the Asian-Pacific region, he
said, adding that the friendship and exchanges between the two
peoples date back to ancient times.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, he went on to say, with the concerted efforts
of both sides, the relations between the two nations have gained a
good momentum of all-round development.
</P>
<P>
"The bilateral high-level exchanges have been frequent. The
friendly exchanges and cooperation in various fields have
progressed smoothly with remarkable results," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
As the two economies are highly complementary to each other, he
continued, there are broad prospects for the further expansion of
the mutually-beneficial bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"It is all the more important for China and Australia, both
important countries in the Asian-Pacific region, to strengthen
contacts and develop cooperation further at the turn of the
century," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
This is not only in the common interests of the two countries
and two peoples, but also conducive to maintaining and promoting
peace and development in the region, the president explained.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that being one of the oldest states and cities in
Australia, the state of Victoria and the city of Melbourne are
abundant in natural resources.
</P>
<P>
They boast a picturesque landscape, advanced agriculture,
animal husbandry, manufacturing and financial industries, and
occupy an important position in history and play an important role
in the national economic development of Australia, he said.
</P>
<P>
Victoria and Melbourne have long served as pivotal links in the
friendly exchanges between China and Australia, playing a positive
role in the development of Sino-Australian relations, Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
