<HEADLINE> Macao Police Seize Large Quantities of Pirated CDs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Macao marine police detected 23,
000 pieces of pirated compact disks Sunday night and one man was
detained for further investigations, the Macao Daily News reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
At around nine o'clock Sunday night, a truck was driven to a
local dock, loaded with 28 wood cases, which were claimed to
contain electric motors to be shipped to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Police opened one case and lit it up with a flashlight, finding
that shining lights were reflected from a crevice. As the
suspicious motor was dismantled, police saw roles of CDs inside.
</P>
<P>
Police dismantled all the cases and detected a total of 23,000
pieces of pirated CDs, most of which were video products.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the marine police said that more than 800,000
pieces of pirated CDs have been detected this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
