<HEADLINE> Share Prices Edge Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed on
Singapore Stock Market Monday as later profit-taking eroded early
gains.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) trimmed 6.60 points to
end at 2,099.78 points in thin dealing.
</P>
<P>
The total volume contracted to 192.53 million shares valued at
373.77 million Singapore dollars (221.52 million U.S. dollars).
Losers outpaced gainers by 197 to 122 with 127 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 25.77 million parcel by Gen Int which
was transacted by 0.39 U.S. dollars per share. AFP was the second
most heavily-traded stock with a turnover of 19.16 million units.
GoldenAg was the next with 13.63 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
PacCent was the biggest gainer of the day roaring up 120 cents
to close at 9.50 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 surged up 90 cents
to finish at 17.60 Singapore dollars. NatElec picked up 50 cents
to end at 8.15 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH headed the descent of the day incurring a
loss of 70 cents to end at 27.80 Singapore dollars. Robinson and
SPH 100 shed 50 cents to finish at 5.30 and 27.80 Singapore
dollars respectively. C&AMP;C retreated 50 cent to end at 7.00
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted shares opened higher buoyed by the hefty rise on
Wall Street Friday but profit-taking emerged toward the close and
dragged down the benchmark STI.
</P>
<P>
They attributed today's thin volume to the U.S. Labor Day
Holiday on Monday.
</P>
<P>
They also noted U.S. dollar denominated stocks were the most
actives of the day and bank stock supported the STI gains.
</P>
</TEXT>
