<DOCNO> XIE19990906.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 13:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Guards Kill Man Grazing Egyptian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 6 (Xinhua) -- A man on Monday grazed Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak with a sharp tool as Mubarak drove through
a northern port city. The president's guards gunned down the man,
the government said.
</P>
<P>
"While the president was waving through the car's window, a
person approached the motorcade holding a sharp tool and inflicted
a light wound," said a statement issued by the president's office,
indicating Mubarak was injured on the arm.
</P>
<P>
"The special security guards dealt with the incident
immediately and killed" the unidentified assailant, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak's wound was treated with a disinfectant before the
president went on to a meeting and delivered a speech.
</P>
<P>
One of his guards was hit by a stray bullet and wounded, the
witnesses said. But the government statement said the wound - a
finger cut - was caused when the guard tried to stop the assailant
from reaching the car.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred in Port Said, 180 kilometers northeast of
Cairo, at the northern end of the Suez Canal, where Mubarak was
inspecting industrial projects.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian television later showed videotape of crowds on the
streets of Port Said cheering Mubarak, but cut away as shots rang
out and did not show the attack. The next pictures showed Mubarak
at the meeting hall, where supporters clapped and chanted "Mubarak
is the people's beloved! We salute you Mubarak."
</P>
<P>
Mubarak said nothing about the attack in a speech devoted to
economic development.
</P>
<P>
The most serious of the attacks on Mubarak came in June 1995,
when Muslim militants fired on his limousine as it was driving out
of the airport of Addis Ababa of Ethiopia on the way to a summit
of the Organization of African Unity.
</P>
<P>
His predecessor, President Anwar Sadat, was assassinated in
1981 by Islamic militants angered at his having signed a peace
treaty with Israel in 1979. Mubarak, who was Sadat's vice
president, became president after the assassination.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak plays a key role in mediating the Arab-Israeli peace
talks and has helped the Palestinians and Israel reach several
peace agreements. The latest is the memo for the implementation of
the Wye accord, which was signed in Egypt between the two sides
early Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak has severely cracked down the Islamic militants who has
attempted since 1992 to topple the secular Egyptian government and
install a strict Islamic rule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
