<HEADLINE> Chinese Postcards For The Year Of The Elderly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Zhengzhou, capital of
central China's Henan Province, has issued a set of five postcards
for the International Year of the Elderly.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations reports that the elderly now account for one
out of every ten people in the world.
</P>
<P>
The postcards have a theme of respect and concern for the
elderly and every set includes a 20-yuan (about 2.5 U.S. dollar)
accidental insurance policy. With this policy, the buyer or the
recipient of the set of postcards will get 10,000 yuan of
insurance indemnity in case of an accident.
</P>
<P>
They are backed by the provincial bureau for elderly officials,
the Zhengzhou branch of China Pacific Insurance Co. Ltd., and the
Zhengzhou Post Office.  
