<HEADLINE> Moscow Blast Victim Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 6 (Xinhua) -- One of the victims of the
August 31 blast in a mall under Moscow's Manezh Square near the
Kremlin died Sunday, the Itar-Tass news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Russian woman and her Lebanese husband were
spending their honeymoon and were near the mall's video game
arcade, where an estimated equivalent of 300 grams of TNT went off,
leaving 44 people injured.
</P>
<P>
Her husband, with burns of over 70 percent of his body surface,
remains in critical condition in the Sklifosofsky Institute of
Intensive Care, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
Police are still investigating the explosion, and Islamic
militants related to the breakaway republic of Chechnya were seen
as one of the possible perpetuators of the attack.
</P>
<P>
Law enforcement officers also discovered leaflets claimed to be
authored by an anti-consumerism group that hails "city guerrilla
warfare" aimed at creating a "revolutionary situation" in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
