<HEADLINE> Kenya's Ruling Party Wins Two More Seats in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The ruling Kenya African
National Union (Kanu) has won two more seats in the just
concluded parliamentary by- elections, therefore consolidating its
dominant position in the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
The seats from constituencies in East Province, previously held
by the opposition Democratic Party, were captured by Kanu in
Saturday's by- elections.
</P>
<P>
Kanu has obtained 121 seats among the total of 222, while the
major opposition Democratic Party reducing its seats from 41 to
38, Daily Nation reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
In the by-elections for local councils, Kanu also took 11 out
of 15 seats countrywide, even in strongholds of the opposition
parties.
</P>
<P>
Although there is much criticism against the ruling party over
 corruption, poor governance and low efficiency, no opposition
parties are able to pose a menace to Kanu in the east African
country.  
