<DOCNO> XIE19990906.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia Limits Truck Weight to Protect Roads, Bridges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 6 (Xinhua) -- In order to protect roads
and bridges, the Cambodian government introduced a new measure
last week to limit the weight of transport trucks.
</P>
<P>
According to a sub-decree approved by the Council of Ministers
last Friday, the trucks that exceed the weight limit by 5 to 10
percent will be fined 100,000 riel (about 25 U.S. dollars) and the
trucks that are more than 10 percent over the limit will be fined
25 U.S. dollars per ton. Offenders will not be allowed to proceed
until the fine is paid.
</P>
<P>
The weight limit will vary, depending on the type of trucks.
</P>
<P>
Five vehicle scales had already been set up last month on
National Route 6 between Phnom Penh and Siem Reap town and
National Route 7 between Capital Phnom Penh and Stung Treng.
</P>
<P>
The move, it was said, has achieved some success that fewer
overweight trucks are now being caught, but it is impossible to
completely stop the problem. Stronger enforcement is needed,
according to an official of the Transport Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
