<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis, Williams Advance to Quarterfinals at U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Teenagers Martina Hingis and
Venus Williams overcame long-time tour veterans in fourth-round
action Sunday, moving one step closer to an expected semifinal
showdown at the U.S. Open Tennis.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, the top seed and 1997 champion, continued her mastery
of 10th seed and 1994 champion Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario of Spain
with a hard-fought 6-4, 7-5 win.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old Williams, who lost the Open final to Hingis in
her debut two years ago and is seeded third this year, came back
to beat fellow American Mary Joe Fernandez 2-6, 6-1, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
In other fourth-round matches invloving seeded women, No. 12
Barbara Schett of Austria earned a quarterfinal meeting with
Williams by crushing Elena Likhovtseva of Russia 6-0, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Unseeded Anke Huber of Germany ousted her second consecutive
seed when she took out Australian Open runner-up and 15th seed
Amelie Mauresmo of France 6-4, 6-4. Huber, who knocked off No. 8
Jana Novotna of the Czech Republic in the third round, will meet
Hingis in the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
The start of play was delayed more than two hours due to rain
this morning and rain twice interrupted play during the afternoon,
pushing many matches back into the evening session.
</P>
<P>
Among the men, seventh seed Todd Martin of the United States
needed just 36 minutes to advance to the fourth round earlier
Sunday as Magnus Larsson of Sweden retired with a knee injury
after losing the first set 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Greg Rusedski of Britain ousted unseeded American Chris
Woodruff 7-5, 3-6, 6-3, 6-4 tonight.
</P>
<P>
Among other seeded men in third-round action Sunday night,
fifth seed Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil had little trouble to beat
Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia 6-4, 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Jiri Novak of the Czech Republic advanced to a four-round
meeting with countryman Slava Dosedle, when Fabrice Santoro of
France retired due to injury in the third set of their match.
Dosedel moved on with a victory over Swedish qualifier Fredrik
Jonsson.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Magnus Norman entered the fourth round with Kuerten by
defeating Australia's Richard Fromberg 4-6, 6-3, 6-1, 6-3.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
