<DOCNO> XIE19990906.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese And Turkmen Military Leaders Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, the chief of
General Staff of the People's Liberation Army (PLA), met today
Batyr Sarjayev, Turkmenistan's deputy prime minister and defense
minister.
</P>
<P>
Sarjayev is Turkmenistan's first defense minister to visit
China since the country established diplomatic ties with China
seven years ago.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that Sarjayev's visit opens a new chapter in high-level
military exchanges between the two military services and will lay
a foundation for bilateral friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
Fu explained Chinese government's stance on the Taiwan issue
and said it is the common aspiration of all the Chinese people to
put to an end the separateness of Taiwan and the motherland at an
early date. He emphasized that the PLA will push the country's
reunification cause forward in line with the "one China" principle,
peaceful reunification and the "one country, two systems"
principle.
</P>
<P>
He said that the PLA is ready to safeguard the motherland's
sovereignty and territorial integrity and to crush any attempt to
divide the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Sarjayev said that he hopes his visit will contribute to
friendly cooperation between Turkmenistan and China and that of
the two military services and praised the outstanding achievements
of the PLA in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed Turkmenistan's continued support to the "one
China" policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
