<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills Six in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and
five others critically injured Sunday after a bus overturned in
eastern Kenya, the Daily Nation newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
A rear tyre burst caused the mimi-bus to veer off the road and
roll several times before the vehicle landed on its roof, police
said.
</P>
<P>
The injured, including the driver, were rushed to various
hospitals nearby.
</P>
<P>
Luggage was scattered at the scene where two bodies remained
for hours before they were removed. Police had a difficult time
keeping looters at bay.  
</P>
