<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice President Meets Cote d'Ivoire PM (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice President Hu
Jintao told visiting Cote d'Ivoire Prime Minister Daniel Kablan
Duncan, that the Chinese government supports the bid of Cote d'
Ivoire to host the 23rd Universal Postal Union Congress.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the remark in his meeting with Duncan here this morning
at the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
Duncan arrived in the Chinese capital Sunday to attend the
ongoing 22nd Universal Postal Union (UPU) Congress.
</P>
<P>
Hu told the guests that the Chinese government supported Cote d
'Ivoire's bid as it is an influential country in Africa which
plays an important role in regional and global affairs.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the ongoing UPU Congress, Hu said that the Chinese
government and relevant departments had made every effort to
ensure the success of the congress.
</P>
<P>
He explained to Duncan that Chinese President Jiang Zemin had
attended its opening session and made an opening speech on the
occasion.
</P>
<P>
He considered the congress offered an opportunity for member
states to enhance understanding and friendship and promote
cooperation. "All the combined efforts made a contribution to the
development of world postal services," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990906.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice President Meets Cote d'Ivoire PM (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During the meeting, Hu also recalled his visit to Cote d'Ivoire
earlier this year and again extended his gratitude to the
hospitable reception given by the Cote d'Ivoire government and
Prime Minister Duncan.
</P>
<P>
Hu spoke highly of the friendship and relations of cooperation
between China and Cote d'Ivoire since the establishment of
diplomatic ties some 16 years ago, saying it had witnessed a
smooth growth in the period.
</P>
<P>
"Thanks to the care and promotion given by the leadership of
the two countries, bilateral relations saw further consolidation
in recent years," he said.
</P>
<P>
"China is willing to make concerted efforts with Cote d'Ivoire
in a bid to bring a long-term, stable and energetic Sino-Cote d'
Ivoire relations well into the 21st century," he added.
</P>
<P>
In reply, Duncan said he highly valued Hu's visit paid early
this year, saying that it played an important role in promoting
mutually beneficial cooperation in all fields between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Cote d'Ivoire values the development of high-
calibre relations with China, saying that his country will
unswervingly adhere to the "one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Also, he said his country is willing to strengthen exchanges
and cooperation with China on the human rights issue and other
major issues of principle since the two countries shared similar
views in these regards.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Minister of Information Industry Wu Jichuan and Vice
Foreign Minister Ji Peiding were among those present at the
meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
