<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Egyptian newspapers Monday.
</P>
<P>
Al-Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- World leaders have welcomed the Palestinian-Israeli
agreement for carrying out the Wye Accord, which was signed in
Egyptian Red Sea resort Sharm El Sheikh in the small hours of
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Al-Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and Sultan Qaboos Bin Said
of Oman met again in Sharm El-Sheikh Sunday, discussing the
outcome of the recent contacts among Mubarak, Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat, Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak and U.S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders' talks come within the framework of constant
consultations between the two sisterly countries at the highest
levels and reflect their strong ties and keenness on protecting
Arab higher interests and closing Arab ranks.
</P>
<P>
Al-Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa will head for Libya
Monday for the ministerial meeting of the Organization of African
Unity to set the stage for the extraordinary summit to be held in
Libya on Wednesday and Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Moussa said he will hold intensive talks with a number of
African foreign ministers on African issues of mutual concern,
particularly current conflicts and problems in Africa, in addition
to economic issues that concern Africa.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- The report of the Central Bank of Egypt, released recently,
showed that an increase in the volume of local debts over the past
nine months.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the increase to government debts, which
rose by 14.3 billion Egyptian pounds (4.2 billion U.S. dollars) to
reach 150.6 billion pounds (44.3 billion dollars). 
</P>
