-- Microsoft officially released the Chinese version of its
Office 2000 on the Chinese market last Monday.
</P>
<P>
-- The People's Bank of China (PBOC) and four other state
departments jointly issued a provisional procedure last Monday on
the management of closed-end loans to foreign trade companies,
aiming to give more support to the country's export sector.
</P>
<P>
-- Ecuadorian President Jamil Mahuad said here last Tuesday
that his government wishes to further expand trade and economic
cooperation with China, and that his current state visit to China
will help further boost bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
-- China has made actual use of 288.94 billion U.S. dollars in
funds from overseas since the reform and opening-up policy was
implemented 20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
-- Production of an air-conditioned double-decker train, the
most advanced of its kind in China, was finished last Tuesday in
Nanjing, the capital city of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
-- The China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC), the
watchdog of the futures market, released four documents governing
futures trade last Tuesday to ensure that the Provisional
Regulations on Futures Trade are properly implemented.
</P>
