<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Kills 2, Injuries 18 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 6 (Xinhua) -- A private bus Sunday afternoon
ploughed into a group of garment factory girls, killing two of
them and injuring 18 others in western Sri Lanka, police sources
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Police said the tragedy occurred when the girls were waiting to
board a bus and return home at Yatiyantota, some 70 kilometers
east of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The driver had been driving the vehicle at high speed on a wet
road and was unable to control the bus, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
The deceased girls have been identified as Chandima Subhasini,
28, and Rasika, 26.
</P>
<P>
Four of the 18 injured girls who were in serious condition have
been transferred to the Colombo National Hospital. The rest have
been sent to local hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the bus had fled the scene soon after the
accident but has been identified. Police were conducting further
investigations to arrest the driver, the sources added. 
