<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Rice Export Likely to Top 4M Tons in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam expects to export 4.2
million tons of rice this year, 200,000 tons more than the
original forecast of the Vietnamese government.
</P>
<P>
This, according to a report of Vietnam News Monday, is based on
an anticipated increased harvest and the turnover of Vietnam's
finished rice export.
</P>
<P>
The rice exports of the country already stood at 3.4 million
tons by the end of August.
</P>
<P>
The gross output of Vietnam's spring-winter crop this year has
reached 14.04 million tons, 48,000 tons above the previous crop.
</P>
<P>
The final yield of the now-harvested autumn-summer rice crop is
forecast at 8.3 million tons, 800,000 tons higher than last
year's.
</P>
<P>
About 200,000 tons of rice are in storage.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Trade Ministry estimated that Vietnam will export
400,000 to 500,000 tons of processed rice this month.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam exported 3.8 million tons of rice last year and was the
second biggest rice exporter in the world. 
</P>
