<HEADLINE> Doohan Faces Three-week Wait after Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, IMOLA, Italy, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Motorcycling world
champion Mick Doohan will wait for another three weeks before
deciding whethe his latest operation will allow him to return to
the track.
</P>
<P>
The Australian 500cc champion, who broke his left wrist and
right leg and shoulder in Spain in May, had surgery in the United
States on Friday to remove a plate and six screws inserted during
initial corrective surgery three months ago.
</P>
<P>
Doohan, champion for the past five years but now out of the
running to retain the title this season, said last month that the
lack of movement and strength in his arm was what was holding back
his return.
</P>
<P>
The Australian said that he might attend the Valencia Grand
Prix in Spain later this month as a spectator but would then
return to Australia, which has a grand prix on October 3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
