<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar-Singapore Trade Grows in 1998-99 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Bilateral trade between Myanmar
and Singapore reached as high as 972.45 million U.S. dollars in
fiscal 1998-99 which ended in March, 10.74 percent more than that
of the previous fiscal year which was 878.12 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figures published by Myanmar's Central
Statistical Organization, of the total bilateral trade in the
1998-99, Myanmar's imports from Singapore stood at 861.6 million
dollars, up 16.43 percent compared with the figure of the previous
fiscal year which was 740 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's exports to Singapore in the 1998-99 amounted to only
110.85 million dollars, down by 19.74 percent compared with the
previous fiscal year which was 138.12 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Singapore not only tops the list of exporters to Myanmar but
also stands as one of the leading investors in the country.
</P>
<P>
Other official statistics show that Singapore's investment in
Myanmar totaled 1.087 billion dollars in 46 projects during the
five-year period from April 1994 to April 1999, accounting for
15.31 percent of the 7.1 billion dollars' total foreign investment
 absorbed since late 1988 when Myanmar began to adopt the
open-door economic policy.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is the second largest foreign investor after Britain
out of 24 countries and regions investing in Myanmar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
