<HEADLINE> Myanmar-Thailand Trade Tops 400M Dollars in 1998-99 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Bilateral trade between Myanmar
and Thailand came to 434.93 million U.S. dollars in fiscal 1998-99
which ended in March, an increase of 21.56 percent over the
previous fiscal year which was 357.79 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest Economic Indicators published by
Myanmar's Central Statistical Organization, of the total bilateral
trade, Myanmar's imports from Thailand amounted to 358.8 million
dollars in 1998-99, increasing by 53.99 percent compared with the
figure in the previous fiscal year which was 232.99 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
During the fiscal year, Myanmar's exports to Thailand stood at
76.13 million dollars, falling by 38.99 percent compared with the
previous fiscal year which was 124.8 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Thailand ranked the second after Singapore in its export to
Myanmar among the member countries of the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations.
</P>
<P>
During the five-year period from April 1994 to April 1999,
Thailand's investment in Myanmar reached 961.2 million dollars in
27 projects, accounting for 13.53 percent of the 7.1 billion
dollars' total foreign investment absorbed since late 1988 when
Myanmar began to adopt the open-door economic policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
