<HEADLINE> Indonesia Ready to Host 2006 Asiad, Says Sports Chief) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's National Sports
Council (KONI) General Chairman Wismoyo Arismunandar Sunday
reiterated Indonesia's readiness to host the 15th Asian Games in
the year 2006.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready for that though we must of course see that our
country's situation and condition are good. We are not too rigid,"
Wismoyo said in Pekanbaru, capital of Riau.
</P>
<P>
To be able to host the games, Indonesia should have a strong
commitment to developing its own sports.
</P>
<P>
"Only with such strong commitment, were will be trusted by
other Asian countries to hold the Asian Games," the chief was
quoted by the Antara News Agency Monday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Besides Indonesia, Malaysia and Qatar are among the Asian
countries to bid for hosting the regional Olympic style games.
</P>
<P>
On Malaysia's wish that Indonesia abandons its plan to host the
games, Wismoyo said Jakarta and Kuala Lumpur must talk about it.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's dismal performance at the recent Southeast Asian (
SEA) Games in Brunei has prompted Minister of Sports and Youth
Affairs Agung Laksono to call for yet another review over the
country's planned bid to host the 2006 Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia was dealt a blow at the biennial Southeast Asian
sporting event last August, ending in third place behind Thailand
and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
"What we are left with now is how to upgrade performance. We'd
better keep the aspiration of how Indonesia can become the host of
the 2006 Asian Games," Agung said here last week.
</P>
<P>
However, Agung rejected a further idea that he might as well
call for a halt to the plan, bearing in mind that the effort would
need a huge amount of money while the prospect looks gloomy.
</P>
<P>
The 14th Asian Games will be held in the South Korean city of
Pusan in 2002, while the 13th was held in Bangkok, Thailand, last
year.
</P>
<P>
In the last Asian Games, in which some 6,000 athletes from 41
countries and regions took part, Indonesia grabbed six gold, 12
silver and 17 bronze medals. 
</P>
