<HEADLINE> Houston Beats New York to Win 3rd WNBA Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Inspired by the memory of former teammate Kim Perrot, who died
of cancer on August 19, and stung by Teresa Weatherspoon's miracle
game-winning shot from beyond midcourt that evened the series for
New York on Saturday, the Comets stifled the Liberty with a
standout defensive performance.
</P>
<P>
"We won this for the memory of Kim. This has been a wonderful
time winning back to back to back," said Cynthia Cooper, who
garnered her third straight WNBA Championship Most Valuable Player
award after a 24-point performance.
</P>
<P>
