game was the sweetest it's ever been. Give New York credit, they
did an amazing job."
</P>
<P>
Houston, which improved to 7-0 when facing elimination in the
WNBA playoffs, held New York to 7-of-30 (23.3 percent) shooting in
the second half and 31 percent (17-of-55) overall.
</P>
<P>
The Comets held the Liberty without a basket for a 10:29
stretch bridging the halves and opened a 38-29 lead with 11:54 to
play.
</P>
<P>
Tina Thompson, who finished with 13 points, dealt the crushing
blow as she netted seven points in a 10-0 tear that extended the
Comets' lead to 48-31 at the 4:29 mark.
</P>
<P>
Sue Wicks scored 11 points and Vickie Johnson added nine for
New York, which was thwarted by Houston in the WNBA Finals for the
second time in three years. The Comets also knocked off the
Liberty in the inaugural WNBA Final in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Houston made 27-of-32 free throws while New York only went to
the line nine times, making eight. Cooper was 13-of-15 from the
charity stripe. 
