<HEADLINE> Cartoons Aim to Educate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Professional film animators
have joined forces with scientific experts to create a special
series of cartoon films aimed at teaching youngsters the rudiments
of science.
</P>
<P>
The 300 humorous cartoons, each ten minutes long, feature a
blue cat as the presenter and have been broadcast regularly by
Beijing Television last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Television, also the maker, has used modern video
and film techniques to recreate natural phenomenon and scientific
wonders such as celestial movement, continental drift, volcanic
eruptions, tornadoes and a whole range of other topics including
the structure of molecules and cell division.
</P>
<P>
The series is the first of its kind in China and comes at a
time when the country is promoting the education in science
especially among the young people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
