<DOCNO> XIE19990906.0253 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Martin Advances at U.S. Open as Mauresmo Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Huber, ranked 27th, beat the 15th seed from France 6-4, 6-4 in
70 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Mauresmo saved one match point, then came back and saved two
more, holding serve before Huber served out the match.
</P>
<P>
Huber reached the U.S. Open quarter-finals for the first time
in 10 appearances at Flushing Meadows. This is her best Grand Slam
showing since going to last year's Australian Open semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Martin won in 36 minutes when Sweden's 81st-ranked Magnus
Larsson retired with a knee injury after the American captured the
first set 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Injuries have already cost the 14.5 million-dollar tournament
last year's four men's semi-finalists - champion Pat Rafter, top-
ranked Pete Sampras, Carlos Moya of Spain and Australia's Mark
Philippoussis.
</P>
<P>
Martin advanced into the round of 16 against the winner of a
scheduled match between Britain's Greg Rusedski, the ninth seed,
and American Chris Woodruff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
